+
+| Bus | Sources | Inserts intent | Primary risk |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| KICK | Tok, punch, body, tail print, transient helpers | Tone shaping and layer balancing before joining the sub lane. Kick style: cleaner punch-focused tok and shorter tail. | If the tail is too long or too hot, the reverse bass loses definition and the drop softens. |
+| SUB | Sub sine, reverse bass mono core, low fill support | Mono discipline, low-end cleanup, and phase-safe shaping | Stereo or saturated sub below ~120 Hz will make the drop collapse in mono and blur the limiter. |
+| KICK & BASS | KICK bus + SUB bus | Gentle glue, shared clip control, and final kick/sub balance | Over-compressing this bus steals tok impact and exaggerates tail pumping. |
